{
  "stem": "18102.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You then had to apply to the Russian foreign ministry to leave and grant permission to leave.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my father still didn't come back to Vilna during that period of time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother and I would go, as a routine, on a Friday afternoon, to see if our name was listed among those who were granted permission to leave.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A list would be [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] posted for those who were granted permission.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Posted at the Russian Ministry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we would go there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It wasn't really the Russian Ministry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was just taken over by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was previously the Polish Ministry and then the Lithuanian Ministry and now the Russian Ministry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, that's a little interesting anecdote that I ought to mention, is the fact that in my first grade, in school, I began a, a, a kind of a journey of language that lasted a long, long time.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You must remember that my two early languages were Yiddish and Polish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When I got to, to Vilna and it became Lithuanian, the school was Lithuanian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And Lithuanian became the language that we were being taught.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So this was my third language.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When the Russians took over, the same school-- I was still in first grade, or I was on my way to second, I think-- and the, and the language now became Russian.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "This was my fourth language.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Eventually it was-- by the time I was in-- eligible for third grade I began to learn Japanese.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And by the time I got to the United States-- this whole period of time, as we're talking, is a, is a, a two-year period-- I was learning English.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we're talking about a real confused kid with lots of languages, something like six.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
